Von Ehrenfels studied philosophy at the [[维也纳大学|维也纳大学]] with [[Franz_Brentano|Franz Brentano]] and [[Alexius_Meinong|Alexius Meinong]], promoted under supervision of Meinong, after the latter's move to the [[Karl-Franzens-University|Karl-Franzens-University]] of [[Graz|Graz]], in [[1885|1885]] on the topic of ''Größenrelationen und Zahlen. Eine psychologische Studie'' ("Relations of magnitude and numbers. A psychological study"). He obtained his habilitiation in [[1888|1888]] in Vienna with the work: ''Über Fühlen und Wollen'' ("On feeling and willing").  1896至1929年间，他在[[布拉格德国大学|布拉格德国大学]]担任哲学教授。-->

